The stars that we then want to retain from the original photometry have to simultaneously satisfy the req uired cuts fordiﬀerent qualityparametersin bothwavelengths.These limitsarethefollowing:eachobjectmustbeclassiﬁedasag ood star (meaning a not too extended or too sharp object, quanti- ﬁed by an “object type” that has to be ≤2) and has to be re- covered extremely well in the image (each star has an assigne d “error ﬂag” for that, which we require to be 0 in order to avoid saturation or photometry extending out of the chip), its sig nal to noise ratio has to be at least 5, the sharpness parameter ha s to be|sharp|≤0.3, the crowding parameter is set to a value lower than 0.5(in mag, whichquantiﬁeshow muchbrighterthe 1http://purcell.as.arizona.edu /dolphot/.star would be if isolated when measured), and ﬁnally the χhas to be≤2.5.
